Sample_source_name_ch1: Blood sample from SLE subject at week52 with LY 120 mg Q2W treatment
treatment: treatment (q2w=once in 2 weeks; q4w=once in 4 weeks): LY 120 mg Q2W
adna_anti-dsdna: adna_at_baseline (anti-dsdna level: Negative < 30 IU; Positive  __‚ 30 IU): Positive
Sample_characteristics_ch1.12: c3base (low < 0.9 g/l; normal >= 0.9 g/l; h = high): N
Sample_characteristics_ch1.14: c4base (low < 0.1 g/l; normal >= 0.1 g/l; h = high): N
Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: A subset of SLE patients were treated with the BAFF/BLyS-blocking, fully-human IgG4 monoclonal antibody, tabalumab (120 mg Q2W or 120 mg Q4W) for 16 weeks or 52 weeks prior to RNA extraction.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from whole blood (preserved in Tempus tubes) using the PerfectPureTM RNA Blood Kit as recommended by the manufacturer (Five Prime, South San Francisco, CA).
Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at week52 with LY 120 mg Q2W treatment
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_characteristics_ch1.14: c4base (low < 0.1 g/l; normal >= 0.1 g/l; h = high): N
Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: A subset of SLE patients were treated with the BAFF/BLyS-blocking, fully-human IgG4 monoclonal antibody, tabalumab (120 mg Q2W or 120 mg Q4W) for 16 weeks or 52 weeks prior to RNA extraction.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from whole blood (preserved in Tempus tubes) using the PerfectPureTM RNA Blood Kit as recommended by the manufacturer (Five Prime, South San Francisco, CA).
Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at week52 with LY 120 mg Q2W treatment
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at week16 with LY 120 mg Q4W treatment
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_characteristics_ch1.12: c3base (low < 0.9 g/l; normal >= 0.9 g/l; h = high): L
Sample_characteristics_ch1.14: c4base (low < 0.1 g/l; normal >= 0.1 g/l; h = high): N
Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: A subset of SLE patients were treated with the BAFF/BLyS-blocking, fully-human IgG4 monoclonal antibody, tabalumab (120 mg Q2W or 120 mg Q4W) for 16 weeks or 52 weeks prior to RNA extraction.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from whole blood (preserved in Tempus tubes) using the PerfectPureTM RNA Blood Kit as recommended by the manufacturer (Five Prime, South San Francisco, CA).
Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at week52 with LY 120 mg Q2W treatment
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: A subset of SLE patients were treated with the BAFF/BLyS-blocking, fully-human IgG4 monoclonal antibody, tabalumab (120 mg Q2W or 120 mg Q4W) for 16 weeks or 52 weeks prior to RNA extraction.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from whole blood (preserved in Tempus tubes) using the PerfectPureTM RNA Blood Kit as recommended by the manufacturer (Five Prime, South San Francisco, CA).
Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at week16 with LY 120 mg Q2W treatment
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at baseline
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at baseline
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. adna_anti-dsdna: adna_at_baseline (anti-dsdna level: Negative < 30 IU; Positive  __‚ 30 IU): Positive
Sample_characteristics_ch1.12: c3base (low < 0.9 g/l; normal >= 0.9 g/l; h = high): N
Sample_characteristics_ch1.14: c4base (low < 0.1 g/l; normal >= 0.1 g/l; h = high): N
Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: A subset of SLE patients were treated with the BAFF/BLyS-blocking, fully-human IgG4 monoclonal antibody, tabalumab (120 mg Q2W or 120 mg Q4W) for 16 weeks or 52 weeks prior to RNA extraction.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from whole blood (preserved in Tempus tubes) using the PerfectPureTM RNA Blood Kit as recommended by the manufacturer (Five Prime, South San Francisco, CA).
Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at week16 with LY 120 mg Q2W treatment
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: A subset of SLE patients were treated with the BAFF/BLyS-blocking, fully-human IgG4 monoclonal antibody, tabalumab (120 mg Q2W or 120 mg Q4W) for 16 weeks or 52 weeks prior to RNA extraction.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from whole blood (preserved in Tempus tubes) using the PerfectPureTM RNA Blood Kit as recommended by the manufacturer (Five Prime, South San Francisco, CA).
Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at baseline
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_label_protocol_ch1: Target preparation was performed according to Affymetrix WT Plus amplification protocol (www.affymetrix.com).
Sample_hyb_protocol: The cDNA generated during the amplification step was used in a fragmentation and labeling reaction to generate target for hybridization to the Affymetrix HTA2.0 arrays
Sample_scan_protocol: GeneChips were scanned using the Affymetrix GeneChip Scanner 3000 7G.
Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at week52 with Placebo treatment
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

Sample_description: Gene expression measured in blood sample from SLE subject at week16 with LY 120 mg Q2W treatment
Sample_data_processing: HTA2.0 microarray pre-processing was performed. Probe level microarray data were summarized to two different levels, "gene" level and "exon-group" level. In both cases, the first two steps of the pre-processing were standard background correction and quantile normalization, as done in standard robust multi-array average (22). For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.

For the "gene" level analyses, data were then summarized by the sample effect estimated by robust regression (rlm function in the R MASS package) from a two-way ANOVA model with probe and sample effects. For the "exon-group" analysis (presented in the corresponding data matrix table), data were first summarized to the probeset level (as defined by Affymetrix) and low-expression probesets were filtered out as follows. An expression score was constructed for each probeset by computing the 80th percentile across all samples; probesets whose expression score was below the 95th percentile of the intronic normalization control probesets (normgene->intron) were discarded. The filtered probesets within a "transcript cluster" were then grouped using hierarchical clustering to form exon groups using the R hclust function. The distance metric between two probesets was defined as one minus the correlation of the pair. Probe level data were then summarized for each "exon-group" (cluster) using robust estimates of the sample effects as done in the "gene" level summarization.
